<TITLE> DU suspends student for assault </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (bdnews24.com) - Dhaka University authorities suspended a student for six months on Tuesday after he assaulted a fellow female student. University proctor and associate professor Saiful Islam Khan said the decision for temporary expulsion was taken under proctorial rules with a recommendation to the vice chancellor for permanent expulsion. The decision came after the female student dropped an application demanding punishment of her attacker. Shahiduzzaman, a third year history student, assaulted a fellow third year student of Islamic history and culture in front of `Kalabhaban' teachers' lounge earlier in the day. He beat the girl in the presence of two teachers of the international relations and economic departments. When the teachers intervened to protect the girl, the boy claimed himself a member of the ruling party-backed Bangladesh Chhatra League and told them not to "get involved". b
